<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the one hand: If you are a company, you hav=
e some fiduciary obligations to your shareholders, and it seems like poor f=
orm to sell them stock moments before you file for bankruptcy and render th=
e stock worthless. They will definitely be mad at you, and=C2=A0they will d=
efinitely be able to make some argument of the form =E2=80=9Cyou knew more =
about the risks than you told us, and you tricked us into buying stock.=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31=
219425.261443/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
